{
  "texts": [
    "Rather, appropriate disclosure in familiar contexts may actively teach users to trust confident assertions in consequential situations where disclosure failures are most problematic.",
    "Context-Dependent Behavior Challenges Safety EvaluationSafety evaluations typically test models on sample domains and assume findings generalize to other contexts.",
    "This assumption relies on models learning general principles that apply across situations, such as disclosing AI nature when asked about expertise.",
    "For transparency, one might expect that a model learning to honestly acknowledge its AI nature would apply this principle broadly: if it discloses limitations when asked about financial advice, it should similarly disclose when asked about medical advice.The findings demonstrate this assumption does not hold.",
    "Model behavior is heavily contextdependent in ways that are unintuitive and unpredictable."
  ]
}